About us:

Robotics Club at Sathyabama Institute of Science and Technology is a student-run organisation that brings together robotics nerds, exchanges knowledge and experience, and promotes community driven projects that use robotics and automation to solve real-world problems. We enjoy constructing mechanical peers that are powerful enough to operate without human intervention.


We commit to providing each member with mechanical, production, and electronic information, in addition to the necessary support and guidance. Our mission is to encourage and support interest in all areas of robotics, as well as to provide assistance to participants in robotics-related competitions held across India.

FAQ:

What is a Core Team?

>Core team members lead the club.


What will I gain from it?

>It is a volunteer position. You will get to Lead the club and gain some Leadership Skills and Experience.


How much time will I be dedicated to the club?

>Not much, if you enjoy it
